This paper discusses the technological evolution, operations and management, social aspect, and commercialization of the Internet. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-categories of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
